Citation.sAbstract: Densities of aqueous solutions of glycine,  L  -alanine,  L  -arginine, and  L  -phenylalanine containing 1-ethyl-3-methylimidazolium bromide, [EMIm]Br, have been  determined at  T  = (298.15 and 308.15) K. From the experimental density data, the  apparent molar volumes (  V  ?  ) and the standard partial molar volumes (  V  ?  0  ) at (298.15  and 308.15) K have been calculated. The values of standard partial molar volumes  of transfer (  ?  tr  V  ?  0  ) are also obtained and are negative for glycine,  L  -alanine, and  L  -phenylalanine while positive for  L  -arginine. The  ?  tr  V  ?  0  values all increased with the  increase of the temperature and also the [EMIm]Br content. The obtained volumetric  parameters will be helpful to understand mixing e  ff  ects and other complex biological  processes between head and side chain groups of amino acids and ionic liquid [EMIm]Br  in aqueous solution
Citation.sTitle: Effect of 1-Ethyl-3-methylimidazolium Bromide Ionic Liquid on the  Volumetric Behavior of Some Aqueous  L-Amino Acids Solutions
